Awesome opportunity.

I keep coming back to whether we could/should measure just D+I =E2=80=93 =
rather than D+I as a central  part of organisations=E2=80=99 values.

I worry that when the review request comes in it will say =E2=80=93 =
=E2=80=9CNow complete your Indigometrics D+I survey where you assess =
your peers=E2=80=99 actions for their level of D+I adherence=E2=80=9D =
=E2=80=93 I don=E2=80=99t think it works?

Maybe its just semantics =E2=80=93 we could call it a =
=E2=80=9CRespect=E2=80=9D solution for example.

I am also struggling a bit with a single definition of D+I, as a basic =
example, should we ask:

=20

*	Chris treats everyone the same no matter their station in life
*	Chris treats others how he would like to be treated himself

=20

Or

=20

*	Chris treats everyone how they would like to be treated

=20

I think D+I will be defined differently at different organisations?

=20

C

